description: Humanity's encounters with the deadly extraterrestrial "bugs" have had distastrous, lethal results. But how did this species spread across the galaxy? Find out in "The Theory of Aliens Propagation," by Aliens: Outbreak writer Mark Verheiden (screenwriter of The Mask, TimeCop, Battlestar Galactica) and artist Mark A. Nelson. And in "The Alien," the xenomorph infestation that rendered Earth all but uninhabitable in Outbreak comes to a head as the exiled human population negotiates with the "Space Jockey" species intent on exterminating the infesting xenomorphs—and Earth!
name: Theory of Alien Propagation/The Alien

description: The Complete Wash Tubbs and Captain Easy by Roy Crane were published by the Flying Buttress Classics Library. Widely considered to be one of the first great adventure strips, Wash Tubbs the wise-cracking, girl-chasing opportunist and soldier of fortune Captain Easy are back for more fun and adventure. Volume 11 (1936-1937) reprints Crane's classic comic strips. Out of money, Wash and Easy join the circus and Lulu Belle gets married. While in Easy's own strip, the adventurer is captured only to be rescued by pigs and then heads for America.

description: Byron is on the road, exploring the back roads and the wild parts of America, searching for his missing brother, but where does one even start looking for a talkative two-headed pickled punk? America is a big place after all. After finding himself at Paradise Acres Trailer Park, he comes across the Mystery of the Fashionable Hillbilly. Is this case too big for the newly self-described 'Psychic Investigator'? Also, on a bus trip going Anywhere, Byron meets a man claiming to be Satan. What is he doing here, why did he let himself go so much, and is there any chance Byron can get his autograph?

description:
Over 300 pages of timeless terror from a master storyteller! Horror comics visionary and coloring pioneer Richard Corben has been a voice of creativity and change for over four decades. For the first time ever, Corben’s legendary Creepy and Eerie short stories and cover illustrations are being collected into one deluxe hardcover! With an informative foreword by artist and comic book colorist José Villarrubia—who also provides color restoration—this volume features Richard Corben’s original stories, Edgar Allan Poe adaptations, and collaborations with cast of comic-book writers.

Essential stories and illustrations from Richard Corben!

The first collection of all of Corben’s legendary Creepy and Eerie stories!

Hard Cover compilation of Corben's work for Eerie and Creepy
name: HC
